❤️‍🩹👴 Health Monitoring System for Elderly

📌 Problem Statement:
Elderly people often live alone and lack immediate access to health monitoring
and emergency alerts. Delayed detection of health issues can be life-threatening. 🚨💔

🎯 Objective:
Create a wearable IoT system that continuously monitors pulse rate 💓,
body temperature 🌡️, and fall detection 🤸, and sends instant alerts
if abnormalities are detected — keeping loved ones safe! 🛡️

🛠️ Hardware & Software Requirements:
• 📶 NodeMCU ESP8266 (Wi-Fi microcontroller)
• 💓 Pulse Sensor (heart rate monitoring)
• 🌡️ DHT11 Sensor (body/ambient temperature)
• 📐 MPU6050 Accelerometer & Gyroscope (for fall detection)
• 📱 Blynk or ThingSpeak (cloud dashboard & notifications)

🔬 How It Works:
1️⃣ Sensors continuously read pulse rate, temperature, and motion data
2️⃣ Data is processed by NodeMCU and sent to the cloud ☁️
3️⃣ If heart rate is abnormal ⚠️ or a fall is detected 🆘, an emergency alert is sent
4️⃣ Caregivers and medical professionals receive real-time notifications 📲

🏆 Expected Outcome:
A compact, wearable health monitoring system that provides peace of mind 🧘
to families by sending real-time health status and emergency alerts
to caregivers or medical professionals. A true life-saver! 🏥💪

